parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the alternator can cause the vehicle to stall or not start, leading to a loss of power and potentially causing an accident.
symptoms: The alternator fails
causing the vehicle to stall or not start
smoke or fire from the alternator
burning odor
and clicking noise when trying to start the vehicle.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the fuel pump relay can cause the vehicle to stall or not start, leading to a loss of power and potentially causing an accident.
symptoms: The vehicle stalls or does not start
hesitation when accelerating
difficulty starting the vehicle
and warning lights on the dashboard.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the electrical system can cause the vehicle to stall or not start, leading to a loss of power and potentially causing an accident.
symptoms: The vehicle stalls or does not start
warning lights on the dashboard
loss of power steering and brakes
and difficulty restarting the vehicle.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the TIPM can cause the vehicle to stall or not start, leading to a loss of power and potentially causing an accident.
symptoms: The vehicle stalls or does not start
warning lights on the dashboard
loss of power steering and brakes
and difficulty restarting the vehicle.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The delay in recall repair can cause the vehicle to continue operating with a known safety defect, potentially leading to an accident.
symptoms: The vehicle owner receives notification of a recall but the parts are not available
or the dealer is unable to perform the repair.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Engine stalling can cause loss of power, loss of brakes, and loss of power steering, leading to accidents or near-misses.
symptoms: Engine stalling while driving
especially when making turns or braking
loss of electrical power
including brakes and power steering.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Fuel pump relay failure can cause the engine to stall, leading to accidents or near-misses.
symptoms: Engine stalling
difficulty starting the engine
fuel pump relay failure.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Camshaft and lifter failure can cause engine misfires, leading to drivability issues and potential engine damage.
symptoms: Engine misfires
tapping or knocking noise
camshaft and lifter failure.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Alternator failure can cause the engine to stall, leading to accidents or near-misses.
symptoms: Alternator failure
engine stalling
smoke or flames from under the hood.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Oil filter adaptor housing recall can cause oil leaks, leading to engine damage.
symptoms: Oil leaks
engine damage
oil filter adaptor housing failure.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: A/C condenser-transmission cooler assembly failure can cause fluid leaks, leading to engine damage.
symptoms: Fluid leaks
A/C condenser-transmission cooler assembly failure.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the brake booster can cause the brake pedal to seize or fail to engage, leading to loss of braking power, which can result in accidents or injuries.
symptoms: The brake pedal seizes or fails to engage
the brake pedal is soft or spongy
the brake pedal does not return to its normal position
the brake pedal has a delayed return to its normal position.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the fuel pump relay can cause the engine to stall or fail to start, which can lead to accidents or strand the driver.
symptoms: The engine stalls or fails to start
the vehicle sputters or hesitates to start
the fuel pump relay fails to engage.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the emergency brake cable can cause the parking brake to fail, leading to accidents or injuries.
symptoms: The parking brake fails to engage
the emergency brake cable breaks or fails to operate properly.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the alternator diode can cause the electrical system to malfunction, leading to engine stalling or failure to start.
symptoms: The engine stalls or fails to start
the electrical system malfunctions
the alternator diode fails to operate properly.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the brake hydraulic system can cause the brakes to fail, leading to accidents or injuries.
symptoms: The brake pedal feels soft or spongy
the brake pedal does not return to its normal position
the brake pedal has a delayed return to its normal position
the brake system fails to operate properly.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Delays in recall repairs can cause drivers to continue operating their vehicles with known safety defects, increasing the risk of accidents or injuries.
symptoms: Delays in receiving recall repair parts
lack of communication from dealerships or manufacturers
inability to schedule recall repairs.
